:Person rdf:type owl:Class ;
        rdfs:subClassOf :Entity .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/PersonalDataProtectionAct
:PersonalDataProtectionAct rdf:type owl:Class ;
                           rdfs:subClassOf :LegalResources ;
                           :eli:title "PersonalDataProtectionAct" ;
                           :eli:title_alternative "PDPA" ;
                           rdfs:comment "A class representing personal data protection legislation, including Thailand's Personal Data Protection Act." ;
                           rdfs:label "PersonalDataProtectionAct"@en .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/Personal_Data
:Personal_Data rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:subClassOf :Data ;
               :definition "“Personal Data” means any information relating to a Person, which enables the identification of such Person, whether directly or indirectly, but not including the information of the deceased Persons in particular;"@en ;
               :involves :Data_Subject ;
               :source :ChapterI ,
                       :Section6 ;
               rdfs:comment """“Personal Data” means any information relating to a Person, which enables the identification of such Person, whether directly or indirectly, but not including the information of the deceased Persons in particular;

It excludes the Information of deceased persons""" ;
               rdfs:isDefinedBy """PDPA 
Chapter 1, Section 6""" ;
               rdfs:label "PersonalData" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/Personal_Data_Protection_Policy
:Personal_Data_Protection_Policy rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                 rdfs:subClassOf :Rule ;
                                 :source "Section29" ;
                                 rdfs:comment """Personal Data Protection Policy is an internal document that sets out the processes and procedures the company has implemented to ensure compliance with the PDPA in the processing of personal information.

Purpose: Internal policy governing cross-border transfers within affiliated groups
Certification: Must be reviewed and certified by the Office (PDPC)
Effect: If certified, exempts from §28 adequacy requirement for intra-group transfers
Absent policy: Controller/Processor may still transfer if suitable protection measures are in place (§29 para 3)"""@en ;
                                 rdfs:isDefinedBy "added to answer QA, answer is from the ground truth dataset." ;
                                 rdfs:label "PersonalDataProtectionPolicy"@en ;
                                 rdfs:seeAlso """Section 29 In the event that the Data Controller or the Data Processor who is in the Kingdom of Thailand has put in place a Personal Data protection policy regarding the sending or transferring of Personal Data to another Data Controller or Data Processor who is in a foreign country, and is in the same affiliated business, or is in the same group of undertakings, in order to jointly operate the business or group of undertakings. If such Personal Data protection policy has been reviewed and certified by the Office, the sending or transferring of Personal Data to a foreign country, which is in accordance with such reviewed and certified Personal Data protection policy, can be carried out and shall be exempt from compliance with section 28.

The Personal Data protection policy, the nature of the same affiliated
undertaking or affiliated business in order to jointly operate the undertaking or business, and the rules and methods for the review and certification in paragraph one shall be as prescribed and announced by the Committee.

In the absent of a decision by the Committee in accordance with section 28, or
the Personal Data protection policy referred in paragraph one, the Data Controller or the Data Processor may send or transfer the Personal Data to a foreign country in exemption to compliance with section 28, if the Data Controller or the Data Processor provides suitable protection measures which enable the enforcement of the data subject’s rights, including effective legal remedial measures according to the rules and methods as prescribed and announced by the Committee."""@en .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/PoliticalOpinions
:PoliticalOpinions rdf:type owl:Class ;
                   rdfs:subClassOf :Sensitive_Personal_Data ,
                                   [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                     owl:onProperty :requiresConsent ;
                                     owl:someValuesFrom :ExplicitConsent
                                   ] ;
                   :source :Section26 ;
                   rdfs:comment "Political opinion data is a category of sensitive personal data under PDPA Section 26. It generally requires explicit consent unless a legal exception applies."@en ;
                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "Section 26" ;
                   rdfs:label "PoliticalOpinions"@en .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/PrivacyNotice
:PrivacyNotice rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:subClassOf :Rule ;
               :source "Section 23" ;
               rdfs:comment """Privacy Notice is a publicly available document that communicates personal information to individuals about individuals whose personal information is collected.

Purpose: Inform data subjects before or at time of collection
Required elements: Purpose, legal basis, data types & retention, recipients, controller contact, data subject rights
Signature required?: No — not mandated by PDPA""" ;
               rdfs:isDefinedBy "added to answer QA, answer is from the ground truth dataset." ;
               rdfs:label "PrivacyNotice" ;
               rdfs:seeAlso """Section 23 In collecting the Personal Data, the Data Controller shall
inform the data subject, prior to or at the time of such collection, of the following details, except
the case where the data subject already knows of such details:
(1) the purpose of the collection for use or disclosure of the Personal Data,
including the purpose which is permitted under section 24 for the collection of Personal Data
without the data subject's consent;
(2) notification of the case where the data subject must provide his or her
Personal Data for compliance with a law, or contract, or where it is necessary to provide the
Personal Data for the purpose of entering into the contract, including notification of the possible
effect where the data subject does not provide such Personal Data;
(3) the Personal Data to be collected and the period for which the Personal
Data will be retained. If it is not possible to specify the retention period, the expected data
retention period according the data retention standard shall be specified;
(4) the categories of Persons or entities to whom the collected Personal Data
may be disclosed;
(5) information, address, and the contact channel details of the Data Controller,
where applicable, of the Data Controller's representative or data protection officer;
(6) the rights of the data subject under section 19 paragraph five, section 30
paragraph one, section 31 paragraph one, section 32 paragraph one, section 33 paragraph one,
section 34 paragraph one, section 36 paragraph one, and section 73 paragraph one.""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/Process
:Process rdf:type owl:Class ;
         rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/Processing
:Processing rdf:type owl:Class ;
            rdfs:subClassOf :Data_Activity ;
            :involves :Data_Controller ,
                      :Personal_Data ;
            rdfs:comment "Implementing measures to protect data and notifying the PDPC and data subjects of any breaches." ;
            rdfs:isDefinedBy "Section 37" ;
            rdfs:label "DataSecurityAndBreachNotificationActivity" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/Processor_Obligation
:Processor_Obligation rdf:type owl:Class ;
                      rdfs:subClassOf :Obligation ;
                      :definition "“Section 40 The Personal Data Processor shall have the following duties: (1) carry out activities only pursuant to instructions… (3) prepare and maintain records…”" ;
                      :involves :Data_Processor ;
                      rdfs:comment """Duties of Data Processors: [Section 40]
- Process Personal Data only according to the Data Controller's instructions, unless instructions are unlawful. If a Data Processor fails to comply, they may be regarded as a Data Controller for that activity.
- Implement appropriate security measures and notify the Data Controller of breaches.
- Maintain records of processing activities.
- An agreement between Data Controller and Data Processor is required to ensure compliance."""@en ;
                      rdfs:isDefinedBy "Section 40" ;
                      rdfs:label "ProcessorObligations" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/PublicSectorEntity
:PublicSectorEntity rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:subClassOf :Entity ,
                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                      owl:onProperty :subjectToPDPA ;
                                      owl:someValuesFrom :PersonalDataProtectionAct
                                    ] ;
                    rdfs:comment "A public sector organization or public authority that may collect, use, or disclose personal data and may be subject to PDPA obligations when acting as a Data Controller or Data Processor." ;
                    rdfs:isDefinedBy "PDPA scope / public sector compliance" ;
                    rdfs:label "PublicSectorEntity" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/RacialData
:RacialData rdf:type owl:Class ;
            rdfs:subClassOf :Sensitive_Personal_Data ,
                            [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                              owl:onProperty :requiresConsent ;
                              owl:someValuesFrom :ExplicitConsent
                            ] ;
            :source :Section26 ;
            rdfs:comment "Racial data is a category of sensitive personal data under PDPA Section 26. It generally requires explicit consent unless a legal exception applies."@en ;
            rdfs:isDefinedBy "Section 26" ;
            rdfs:label "RacialData"@en .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/Rectify_Data
:Rectify_Data rdf:type owl:Class ;
              rdfs:subClassOf :Data_Activity ;
              :involves :Data_Controller ,
                        :Personal_Data ;
              rdfs:comment "Correcting personal data at the request of the data subject." ;
              rdfs:isDefinedBy "Section36" ;
              rdfs:label "Rectification" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/ReligiousOrPhilosophicalBeliefs
:ReligiousOrPhilosophicalBeliefs rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                 rdfs:subClassOf :Sensitive_Personal_Data ,
                                                 [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                   owl:onProperty :requiresConsent ;
                                                   owl:someValuesFrom :ExplicitConsent
                                                 ] ;
                                 :source :Section26 ;
                                 rdfs:comment "Religious or philosophical belief data is a category of sensitive personal data under PDPA Section 26. It generally requires explicit consent unless a legal exception applies."@en ;
                                 rdfs:isDefinedBy "Section 26" ;
                                 rdfs:label "ReligiousOrPhilosophicalBeliefs"@en .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/Representative
:Representative rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:subClassOf :Entity ;
                rdfs:comment "A person in Thailand designated by a foreign Data Controller or Processor to act on their behalf" ;
                rdfs:isDefinedBy "Chapter 3, Section 30" ;
                rdfs:label "Representative"@en .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/RestrictionOfUse
:RestrictionOfUse rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf :Data_Activity ;
                  :involves :Data_Controller ,
                            :Personal_Data ;
                  rdfs:comment "Suspending the use of personal data instead of erasure, e.g. during dispute resolution." ;
                  rdfs:isDefinedBy "Section34" ;
                  rdfs:label "RestrictionOfUse" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/Right
:Right rdf:type owl:Class ;
       rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/RightOfAccess
:RightOfAccess rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:subClassOf :Data_Subject_Rights ;
               :involves :DataAccess ,
                         :Data_Subject ;
               rdfs:comment """To request access to and obtain a copy of their Personal Data and to request disclosure of the acquisition of Personal Data obtained without their consent.

[Chapter III, Section 30]"""@en ;
               rdfs:isDefinedBy "[Chapter III, Section 30]" ;
               rdfs:label "RightOfAccess" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/Right_of_Data_Portability
:Right_of_Data_Portability rdf:type owl:Class ;
                           rdfs:subClassOf :Data_Subject_Rights ;
                           :involves :Data_Subject ;
                           rdfs:comment "To receive their Personal Data in a readable and transferable format and to request its transfer to other Data Controllers"@en ;
                           rdfs:label "RightToDataPortability" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/Right_to_Erasure_or_Destruction
:Right_to_Erasure_or_Destruction rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                 rdfs:subClassOf :Data_Subject_Rights ;
                                 :involves :Data_Subject ;
                                 rdfs:comment "To request the erasure, destruction, or anonymization of their Personal Data if it's no longer necessary, consent is withdrawn without other legal grounds, objection rights are exercised, or data was unlawfully processed."@en ;
                                 rdfs:isDefinedBy "Section 33" ;
                                 rdfs:label "RightToErasureOrDestruction" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/Right_to_Object_Processing
:Right_to_Object_Processing rdf:type owl:Class ;
                            rdfs:subClassOf :Data_Subject_Rights ;
                            :involves :DataObjectionActivity ,
                                      :Data_Subject ;
                            rdfs:comment "To object to the collection, use, or disclosure of their Personal Data in specific circumstances, such as for direct marketing, or when collected under certain exemptions unless compelling legitimate grounds exist"@en ;
                            rdfs:isDefinedBy "Section 32" ;
                            rdfs:label "RightToObject" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/Right_to_Rectification
:Right_to_Rectification rdf:type owl:Class ;
                        rdfs:subClassOf :Data_Subject_Rights ;
                        :involves :Data_Subject ,
                                  :Rectify_Data ;
                        rdfs:comment "To request the Data Controller to ensure their Personal Data remains accurate, up-to-date, complete, and not misleading"@en ;
                        rdfs:isDefinedBy "Section 32 Paragraph 3" ;
                        rdfs:label "RightToRectification" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/kyith/ontologies/2025/6/untitled-ontology-33/Right_to_Restriction_of_Use
:Right_to_Restriction_of_Use rdf:type owl:Class ;
                             rdfs:subClassOf :Data_Subject_Rights ;
                             :involves :Data_Subject ,
                                       :RestrictionOfUse ;
                             rdfs:comment "To request the restriction of the use of their Personal Data under certain conditions, for example, while data accuracy is being verified or if the data needs to be retained for legal claims"@en ;
                             rdfs:isDefinedBy "Section 36" ;
                             rdfs:label "RightToRestrictionOfUse" .


